<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880901-0020 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Redken Laboratories Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> RDKN </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   RLI Acquisition Corp. said the Delaware Chancery Court approved the settlement of shareholder litigation resulting from its proposed buy-out of Redken Laboratories Inc., clearing the way for the transaction to be completed.    Under the settlement, RLI increases its offer for the Redken shares it doesn't already own from $34 a share to $34.90. RLI said the offer, at $34.90 a share plus interest, will be extended to 5 p.m. EDT Sept. 13. As of Tuesday, 902,228 shares of Redken common stock had been tendered, RLI said. Redken, a professional hair-care, skin-care and cosmetics company in Canoga Park, Calif., has 2.7 million shares outstanding.    RLI was formed by Paula Kent Meehan, founder and chief executive officer of Redken, and her husband, John E. Meehan, chairman and president, who own 1.3 million, or 48%, of the Redken shares. </TEXT></DOC>